name: Green Bean Casserole I
author: ELENAPFARR
summary: This is a holiday favorite with my family and it's easy to make. It should be a tradition in every household!
ingredients: 2 (15 ounce) cans cut green beans, drained
1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed cream of mushroom soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
In a medium casserole dish mix together green beans, milk, cream of mushroom soup, and 1/2 of the can of onions
Bake for 25 minutes in the preheated oven, until heated through and bubbly
Sprinkle remaining onions over the top, and return to the oven for 5 minutes
Season with salt and pepper to taste
